      "en": "Perennial rosette plant with 1–3 flowering stems 10–50 cm, often branched. Yellow flower heads July–November, resembling dandelion. Leaves in basal rosette, toothed to deeply incised. Distinguished from other hawkbits by branched stems. Forage plant for bees.",
