      "en": "Creeping perennial 10–30 cm, densely hairy. Lilac-blue flowers in dense erect racemes May–August. Leaves ovate, hairy, toothed. Formerly used medicinally for respiratory conditions. Characteristic species of dry, species-rich heath habitats.",
